channel.description: This is a randomly ordered feed of the most recent entries from DTO, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Trump Treasury Sec. Bessent to speak with Chinese trade counterpart on Friday
item.description: Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent will speak by phone on Friday with Chinese Vice Premier He Lifeng, a senior Trump administration official told CNBC.

item.title: Dow industrials, S&P 500, Nasdaq futures point to sharp losses on bank woes
John Bolton indicted; ex-national security advisor is latest Trump foe to face criminal charges
item.description: FBI agents on Aug. 22 raided John Bolton's Maryland home and office in Washington, D.C., as part of a criminal investigation.

item.title: Novo Nordisk, Eli Lilly fall after Trump vows to lower weight-loss drug costs
EU leaders urge swift action on unlocking frozen Russian assets to finance Ukraine, document shows
item.description: EU heads of state will call for quicker action on the use of immobilized Russian assets at a meeting next week, according to a document seen by CNBC.

item.title: American Express beats forecasts, lifts outlook on higher-end consumer spending

item.description: President Donald Trump this week said that he is considering sending Tomahawk missiles to Ukraine to ratchet up pressure on Russia to end the war.

item.title: Dow opens higher as stocks pare large overnight losses on Trump tariff comments
U.S. Chamber of Commerce sues Trump administration over $100,000 H-1B visa fee
item.description: Trump recently imposed a $100,00 fee on temporary visas for highly skilled workers in a push to have American companies hire more domestic workers.
